The paper deals with process calculi and automata, which are typically studied in the area of logic and computation (cs.LO). The focus on security and the need to restrict the scheduler suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a process-algebraic framework, which falls under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL). The consideration of preorders and precongruences suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses verification, which is a common theme in the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
